Unity Log Viewer — installation marker
=======================================

This file is placed here by the Unity Log Viewer INSTALLER (the .msi or
-setup.exe). It is NOT malware, a backdoor, or telemetry.

What it does:
  It lets the app tell it is an *installed* copy rather than the *portable*
  single-exe build. Only installed copies enable the "Download & install
  automatically" update option, because auto-update runs the installer and
  a portable exe can't sensibly install over itself.

What it contains:
  Nothing but this note. It stores no data and runs no code.

Safe to delete:
  Yes. Deleting it just makes the app treat this copy as portable
  (auto-update turns into a "notify me" link instead).

Source code: https://github.com/bwaynesu/UnityLogViewer
